SETTING UP NEW SYMFONY PROJECT (Linux Command Line)

Notes by Tuija P. / 2019-09-25

*****

# CREATING NEW PROJECT
composer create-project symfony/skeleton [projectname]

# --> Go to project folder 
cd [projectname]
--> Initialize local git repository
git init

# create git repository in github/-lab and connect it to 
# local respository

# --> CLI download; fetch command from the address given in the final 
#     lines of the project creation 


----- INSTALL USEFUL STUFF

composer require server 
composer require annotations 
composer require profiler
composer require twig
composer require symfony/form
composer require symfony/orm-pack
composer require --dev symfony/maker-bundle


----- DISPLAY INFORMATION ABOUT PROJECT

php bin/console about


----- CREATE CONTROLLER

# Controller = the function that will be called 
# whenever anyone goes to this [defined @Route] URL

# Path: src/controller --> [NewController].php

'''
<?php

namespace App\Controller;

// Include libraries

use Symfony\Component\HttpFoundation\Response; // for web 
use Symfony\Component\HttpFoundation\Request;



// The name of the file == the name of the class

class NewController {

}